title: Prep volleyball roundup: Rocori cruises to 11-0 in CLC
text:

Join the Conversation To find out more about Facebook commenting please read the Conversation Guidelines and FAQs Prep volleyball roundup: Rocori cruises to 11-0 in CLC TIMES STAFF REPORT 6:51 a.m. CDT October 21, 2015 Volleyball 
COLD SPRING — Eleanor Holthaus led Rocori with 10 kills and three blocks to lead Rocori past Fergus Falls 3-0 in a Central Lakes Conference volleyball match Tuesday. 
Game scores were 25-13, 25-9, 25-9. 
Abby Templin finished with eight kills and 10 digs for the Rocori, Breanna Schouviller added seven kills and Abby Lieser had 12 digs and two ace serves. 
Rocori stays undefeated in the Central Lakes at 11-0 and is 24-1 overall. 
WILLMAR 3, SAUK RAPIDS 2 
WILLMAR — Willmar edged past Sauk Rapids in a Central Lakes Conference match. 
Game scores were 25-21, 13-25, 25-22, 21-25, 15-6. 
Sauk Rapids falls to 6-5 in the CLC and 15-10 overall. 
ST. CLOUD TECH 3, BRAINERD 2 
Junior Paige Fashant led the Tigers with 13 kills in their win over Brainerd at Tech High School. 
Autumn Kubitz added 12 kills and 10 digs and Kate Martig tallied 11 kills for Tech (11-12). 
Game scores were 17-25, 22-25, 25-23, 25-14, 15-12. 
MELROSE 3, BENSON 0 
BENSON — Sandra Sprenger had 14 digs for Melrose in a West Central Conference win over Benson. 
Game scores were 25-17, 25-20, 25-23. 
Rose Johnson added 10 set assists and two service aces for the Dutchmen (18-10 overall). 
ANNANDALE 3, LITCHFIELD 0 
ANNANDALE — Morgan Olson had 12 kills to lead Annandale past Litchfield in a Wright County Conference match. 
Game scores 25-20, 25-21, 25-16. 
Grace Chamberlin had 16 set assists and Brittany Reimer added 14 digs for the Cardinals (20-6 overall). 
LP-GE 3, LITTLE FALLS 1 
LITTLE FALLS — Melanie Dorn finished with 16 kills, 16 set assists and 10 digs in Little Falls’ loss to Long Prairie-Grey Eagle. 
Game scores were 15-25, 25-14, 25-21, 25-13. 
Sydney Berg had 11 kills and Terra Motschke led the Flyers in digs with 19. 
ST. CLOUD CHRISTIAN 3, HOPE CHRISTIAN 1 
ST. PAUL — Leanna Murphy had 24 digs and five kills to lead St. Cloud Christian past Hope Christian. 
Game scores were 25-12, 25-18, 25-27, 25-22. 
Lexi Theisen had 10 digs and five kills and Ellie Petrie had 15 digs and eight kills for the Warriors. Read or Share this story: http://www.sctimes.com/story/sports/high-school/2015/10/21/prep-volleyball-roundup-rocori-cruises-clc-record/74312482/ TOP VIDEOS
